 - are explored for the significance they have for different editorial procedures and their mutual relations to one another. The exploration encompasses theoretical and methodological papers concerned with the superordinate connections obtaining within this conceptual field, papers discussing individual aspects of the conceptual field, and case studies pertaining to individual texts or authors.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aAuthenticationvCongresses. 0aAuthorshipvCongresses. 0aGerman literaturexHistory and criticismvCongresses. 4aAachen ‹2002›. 4aAutorschaft. 4aEdition. 4aLiteratur. 4aTextkritik. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh1 aArnold, Günter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaisch, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarrientos, Joaquín Moreno, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBauer, Elke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBein, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBein, Thomas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBerbig, Roland, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEggert, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEmans, Reinmar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoss, Glenda Dawn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHein, Jürgen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHenke, Silke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHettche, Walter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHofmeister, Wernfried, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.l